FAQ - Create a Business Website

How can I create a small business website for free?

You can create your own site by following these 6 steps:


1. Plan your website. Think about what kind of business youre creating and whos your target audience. With that in mind, you can start mapping out the pages youll want to include like the homepage, About and Contact pages, a blog and services.


2. Build with AI or choose a template. Chat with our AI about your business and instantly get a site thats fully functional and customizable. You can also choose from a huge selection of templates, all designed by professionals with the best practices in mind.


3. Customize your website. You can easily use the drag and drop editor to personalize your site on desktop and mobile. Add business features like a call button, map or payment options so your customers can easily reach you and buy from you instantly.


4. Get a domain name. You can use Wix's domain search to find the perfect domain name. Register an available name or connect an existing one to your new site.


5. Optimize for search engines. With our suite of advanced SEO tools, you can get all the help you need to optimize your site and increase organic traffic.


6. Publish and promote your site. Once youve completed the first five steps, press publish and start bringing in traffic. Make sure to promote your site with built-in marketing tools and streamline your customers site experience with a smart CRM system.

How can I drive relevant traffic to my business site?

There are a variety of strategies to increase relevant traffic to your site and keep visitors engaged once they arrive. Here are five best practices:


1. Optimize your content for SEO. Start by making sure your site is set up to be found by search engines. Then research keywords to find the terms your target audience is looking for. By incorporating those keywords naturally into your content, your site will have a better chance of climbing the ranks on Google, Yahoo and other search engine lists.


2. Integrate with social media. Linking to platforms like Facebook, Instagram and Twitter, will increase traffic to your site. Share your content and engage with your audience regularly to encourage visits. You can also display your social feeds directly on your site, making it easier for visitors to follow you, or add social sharing buttons.


3. Create engaging blog content. Publishing high-quality, relevant blogs is a great way to attract and hold onto visitors. And as long as you blog consistently, your SEO will improve, making your site more discoverable. Make your blog as eye-catching as possible and encourage your readers to leave comments and share.


4. Promote with email marketing. Email marketing campaigns can bring in repeat traffic by keeping your audience up to date with promotions and new content. Personalize your emails, build a subscriber list and offer incentives like discounts and exclusive newsletters.Then track their performance to understand what works and what needs refining.


5. Analyze your traffic. Understanding where your visitors are coming from helps you build better strategies. Monitor useful metrics like page views, bounce rate and average session duration to gauge your sites performance. Wix Analytics allows you to do all of that and more. By regularly reviewing your analytics, you can make smarter decisions about how to boost more traffic.

Is it easy to build a business website?

Yes, Wix offers a few different ways to make a website for a small business, so choose the one thats best for you. Pick from over 900 beautiful templates built with everything you need, or chat with our AI website builder and watch as it creates your fully customizable site in no time.

Will my clients data be secure?

Yes, your site will come with built-in security coveragefrom threat prevention to real-time detection and rapid response. Our world class experts and enterprise-grade security system work 24/7 so you can rest assured knowing that your and your clients information will be kept safe and secure.

Which features should I incorporate when creating a small business website?

You can choose from Wixs wide range of business solutions designed to help you seamlessly build and manage your online businessfrom creating an email address and phone number to built-in analytics and marketing tools. There are also powerful features like the Wix blog maker and online portfolio builder that allow you to showcase your businesss projects and brand voice.

How much does it cost to make a website for a small business?

The price for creating a small business website varies depending on the size of your site, the features you want to include and whether you hire a developer to design your site or choose to do it yourself.


When you consider design expenses, the costs of feature plug-ins, hosting costs and domains costs, you can pay anywhere from an estimated $1,000 to over $10,000.


On Wix, you can build as many business sites as you want for free, but to connect a custom domain and get advanced business features, youll have to upgrade to one of our Premium plans. The cost range is $29-$159 per month, depending on the plan. Other platforms can run up as high as $200, on average.

How long does it take to build a business website?

You can create a simple business website within a couple of hours, while a more complex site can take several weeks or even months to complete.


If youre building your business website yourself, you can expect to spend a few hours on the design and layout. Adding content takes time as well, particularly if youre writing all of it yourself. If you use AI or a site template, it will take considerably less time. You can also use the AI-powered content and image generators to speed up efficiency.

What is the best website builder for a small business?

There are several factors to examine when selecting a great business website builder. You should consider a site builder which not only helps build your website, but also comes with a full set of smart business tools that are easy to use. Features to look for include:


  • A no-code drag and drop website editor that lets you create a unique site quickly and easily with the need to rely on an expensive developer.

  • A platform that comes standard with free and secure hosting, with guaranteed performance and reliability.

  • Built-in tools for managing, marketing and running your business, with no need for extra plug-ins that cost money and require contact care.

  • Multi-channel sales integrations that allow you to promote and sell your products or services on platforms like Google, Facebook, Amazon and other channels, while managing orders from a single dashboard.


Wixs small business website builder fills all of these requirements, offering an ideal solution for both small businesses just starting, and established businesses looking to grow bigger.

Why do small businesses still need a website?

Having a website, even for a small business, is essential. It serves as a reliable home base for your online presence, makes you fully accessible and provides a level of control and professionalism that other mediums like social media alone cant offer. With the right website builder, you get maximum control and customization capabilities so you can streamline every step of running your business.

How do I make my business website look professional?

To make your website look professional, focus on a clean and consistent design with a cohesive color scheme and typography. Use high-quality images and organize your content so its easy to navigate.


In addition to appearance, you should also think about the features that will make your site more appealing to your target audience. Consider adding scheduling software so you can manage appointments online and easily receive payments. If you sell products, youll want to create an online store, which comes with all the professional tools youll need. Plus, the Wix App Market holds a large selection of additional apps like a counter timer, visitor analytics and sophisticated text animation to impress your customers.

How can I increase my business website sales/conversions?

There are several ways to increase your sales online including:

  • Optimizing your product pages. By adding a solid SEO strategy and infrastructure you can drive traffic to your site organically. Read up on SEO resources and visit our SEO Learning Hub for more detailed information.


  • Target shoppers with compelling ads. Adding a campaign thats tailored to your audience will generally earn you a high return on your investment because those are the customers who are most interested in what youre offering.


  • Write compelling content. The stronger your messaging, the more likely youll be able to reach more people and inspire them to shop. Content can include anything from a full-page blog to a meta tag. When it comes to your website, every word counts.


  • Connect with customers. It's important to not overlook relationship building, especially with repeat buyers. Keep them engaged by implementing an Instant live chat, customizing coupons, using smart business automations and including pop-up banners.
